it will show you the all the records
db.students.find({course:"Btech"})

findOne will will give the first matching value
db.students.findOne({course:"Btech"})

if you want to the specific info regsrding about the element (projection)
 db.students.find({course:"Btech"},{name:1,age:1})
or meathod 2
 db.students.find({course:"Btech"}).projection({name:1,course:1,_id:0})

to count
 db.students.find({course:"bsc"}).count()

to sort the collection
db.students.find().sort({age:1})
according to age as example in (assending order 1), (decending oreder -1)

to show limited value
 db.students.find().limit(3)

to skip the upper value with limit
 db.students.find().limit(3).skip(1)

want to find all with course honey
db.students.find({course:{$eq:"bsc"}})

all value less than equal to some vlaue
db.students.find({age:{$lte:30}})

all value not equal to that value
db.students.find({age:{$ne:30}})

similarly with
$gt:greater than equal to
$gte :greater and equal 
$lt:less than
$lte:less than and equal to
$in:[] give all value data whose value in this array
$nin[] give all value data whose value not in this array


using comparision operators in update command
 db.students.updateMany(
         {age:{$lt:30}},
         {$set:{course:"BCA"}}
       );

db.students.deleteMany(
...          {age:{$lt:40}}
...        );
